The article discusses a legislative package proposed by the President in response to the Deepwater Horizon oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico. The package aims to enable the response to the spill to continue efficiently, provide assistance to affected individuals and businesses, and strengthen the oil spill liability system. The proposed legislation includes provisions for immediate funding, food safety monitoring, improving offshore oil exploration, and funding environmental studies. It also includes measures for providing assistance to affected individuals and businesses, such as unemployment assistance, nutrition assistance, and employment assistance. The package also includes provisions for economic recovery, fisheries disaster compensation, and Small Business Administration loans. The article also highlights efforts to hold oil companies responsible, such as raising liability caps and increasing the excise tax that funds the Oil Spill Liability Trust Fund. The proposed legislation also aims to promote program integrity and ensure that aid dollars are spent effectively.